readonly

boolean readonly()
Check if this space is read-only. Read-only flag is set to true for swap snapshots and is usually false for currently active swap space.

Returns:
Read-only flag for this swap space.

iterator

java.util.Iterator<java.util.Map.Entry<K,V>> iterator()
Iterator over swap snapshot in ascending order. If GridCacheSwapSpace.readonly() value is false then Iterator.remove() method is supported, otherwise it will throw UnsupportedOperationException.

This method is identical to calling iterator(true) method.

Specified by:
iterator in interface java.lang.Iterable<java.util.Map.Entry<K,V>>
Returns:
Iterator over swap snapshot in ascending order.

iterator

java.util.Iterator<java.util.Map.Entry<K,V>> iterator(boolean asc)
Iterator over swap snapshot in ascending order. If GridCacheSwapSpace.readonly() value is false then Iterator.remove() method is supported, otherwise it will throw UnsupportedOperationException.

Parameters:
asc - If true then iterator will be in ascending order, otherwise the iterator is in descending order.
Returns:
Iterator over swap space.

forAll

boolean forAll(GridPredicate<java.util.Map.Entry<K,V>> p)
               throws GridException
Loops over the swap space evaluating given predicate for all swapped entries. If this predicate will return false at any point, then iteration will stop and false will be returned out of this method.

Throws:
GridException - If failed.
Parameters:
p - Predicate to check.
Returns:
True if predicate passed for all entries, false otherwise.

put

void put(K key,
         V val)
         throws GridException
Stores key-value pair in this swap space. If key is currently cached, then its value will be updated with given value prior to swapping.

This method is only available if GridCacheSwapSpace.readonly() flag is false.

Throws:
GridException - If failed.
Parameters:
key - Key to swap.
val - Value to swap.

putAsync

GridFuture<?> putAsync(K key,
                       V val)
Asynchronously stores key-value pair in this swap space. If key is currently cached, then its value will be updated with given value prior to swapping.

This method is only available if GridCacheSwapSpace.readonly() flag is false.

Parameters:
key - Key to swap.
val - Value to swap.
Returns:
Future for this operation.

putAll

void putAll(java.util.Map<K,V> map)
            throws GridException
Stores given key-value pairs in this swap space. If any of the keys is currently cached, then its value will be updated with given value prior to swapping.

This method is only available if GridCacheSwapSpace.readonly() flag is false.

Throws:
GridException - If failed.
Parameters:
map - Key-value pairs to swap.

putAllAsync

GridFuture<?> putAllAsync(java.util.Map<K,V> map)
Asynchronously swaps all given key-value pairs in this swap space. If any key is currently cached, then its value will be updated with given value prior to swapping.

This method is only available if GridCacheSwapSpace.readonly() flag is false.

Parameters:
map - Map of key-value pairs to swap.
Returns:
Future for this operation.
